Comment::::<div class="com_user_text">
                            The Clay Sanskrit Library did not come to an end in 2009.  It remains available as a vital series of scholarly publications which are much read, studied and enjoyed (www.claysanskritlibrary.org).  The series consists of 56 published volumes which cover a wide spectrum of Classical Sanskrit literature and are actively promoted by NYU Press.  In addition, the Clay Sanskrit Library sponsors an international outreach program through The Bodleian Library of the University of Oxford and is engaged in discussions with The Bodleian Library to produce a Clay Sanskriut Library anthology.  Although John Clay passed away in 2013, the Clay Sanskrit Library remains a testament to his dedication and commitment to making literature available to the public.
                         </div>



